\noindent The proliferation of decentralized networks is fundamentally constrained by two principal bottlenecks: the economic inefficiency and environmental cost of traditional consensus mechanisms (Proof-of-Work, PoW) and the systemic risks of economic centralization in others (Proof-of-Stake, PoS). Furthermore, current blockchain architectures are unable to perform complex, private, and verifiable off-chain computation, particularly for advanced Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning (AI/ML) inference tasks. The \textbf{NuChain Protocol} introduces a paradigm shift by implementing \textbf{Proof of Thought (PoT)}, a novel consensus mechanism that secures the network through the verification of useful computational and intellectual effort. PoT validators earn the right to propose blocks by successfully generating verified solutions ($\mathcal{S}$) to non-brute-force problems, such as solving complex optimization challenges or executing high-utility zkML inference. Crucially, NuChain integrates \textbf{Zero-Knowledge Machine Learning (zkML)} primitives directly into its execution environment. This enables the trustless, verifiable execution of AI models, ensuring computational integrity without compromising input data privacy or model intellectual property (IP). By fusing PoT's resourceful consensus with zkML's verifiable computation, NuChain establishes a foundation for a truly decentralized, permissionless, and resource-efficient network dedicated to the future of AI-powered decentralized applications (dApps).

